### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

I tried to come up with a way to use the mat datasource (from angular material) with signals so I can update the data depending on the signal source. However, in doing so I came across some weird behavior where I get the below error.

I have created a computed datasource property that wraps a private field/instance of datasource and then have that instances data property set to the value of the signal for my actual data. The issue however is if I use the `viewChild` signal for MatSort or MatPaginator (even without assigning them to the datasource) **AND** have a control flow statement in the template, I get a `ERROR RuntimeError: NG0600: Writing to signals is not allowed in a "computed".` if the data signal changes. If I get rid of the `viewChild` declarations **OR** remove the if-statement in the template, the error doesn't occur.

```ts
interface Item {
  id: number;
  name: string;
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  imports: [MatTableModule, MatButtonModule],
  standalone: true,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  template: `
    <mat-table #table [dataSource]="dataSource()" matSort>

    <ng-container matColumnDef="id">
        <mat-header-cell *matHeaderCellDef mat-sort-header>ID</mat-header-cell>
        <mat-cell *matCellDef="let test">
            <span class="text-truncate">{{test.id}}</span>
        </mat-cell>
    </ng-container>

    <ng-container matColumnDef="name">
        <mat-header-cell *matHeaderCellDef mat-sort-header>Name</mat-header-cell>
        <mat-cell *matCellDef="let test">
          <!-- Getting rid of the if check also resolves the error -->
          @if(test.id) {
            <span class="text-truncate">{{test.name}}</span>
          }
        </mat-cell>
    </ng-container>


    <mat-header-row  *matHeaderRowDef="displayedColumns; sticky: true"></mat-header-row>       


    <mat-row *matRowDef="let test; columns: displayedColumns;"></mat-row>        

   </mat-table>

   <button mat-button (click)="testing()">Test</button>
   <button mat-button (click)="clear()">Clear</button>

  `,
})
export class App {
  // 1.  Click the Test button to reproduce the error

  // 2.  Comment both of these out to resolve runtime error OR comment out the if statement in the template
  public paginator = viewChild(MatPaginator);
  public sort = viewChild(MatSort);

  public displayedColumns = ['id', 'name'];

  readonly testValues = signal<Item[]>([this.newValue()]);

  private _dataSource: MatTableDataSource<Item> = new MatTableDataSource<Item>(
    []
  );

  public dataSource = computed(() => {
    this._dataSource.data = this.testValues();
    return this._dataSource;
  });

  testing() {
    this.testValues.update((val) => [...val, this.newValue()]);
  }

  clear() {
    this.testValues.set([]);
  }

  newValue(): Item {
    let val = {
      id: Math.random(),
      name: crypto.randomUUID(),
    };

    return val;
  }
}

bootstrapApplication(App);
```

